<DOC><DOCNO> AP880418-0275 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-18-88 1550EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-IBM-Metaphor     04-18 0133</FIRST><SECOND>BC-IBM-Metaphor,0139</SECOND><HEAD>IBM Buys Stake In Metaphor Computer; Deal Includes Technology</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   International Business Machines Corp. hasacquired a $10 million stake in Metaphor Computer Systems and willwork with Metaphor on developing business software, the companiesannounced Monday.   Metaphor, a privately held company based in Mountain View,Calif., will cooperate with IBM on rewriting its programs so theywill run on IBM's Personal System-2.   Metaphor makes software that executives can use to analyzemasses of data in an easily understood graphic format. The softwareruns on its own workstations, which use a microprocessor made byMotorola Inc. The project with IBM will allow the software to runon IBM's personal computers, which use Intel Corp. microprocessors.   IBM's stake in Metaphor represents less than 10 percent of thecompany.</TEXT></DOC>